All Classes

  • All Classes Interface Summary Class Summary Enum Summary 
    Class Description
    Actor
    This class will provide the underlying functionality for all actors (chap and his enemies)
    AutoPlayDialogCreator
    Options for auto play, this version only has an exit button
    Block
    This is a block that can be pushed around by Chap.
    ButtonMaker
    Gives a button proper formatting
    Canvas
    Objects of this class provide a simple 2D view of the maze to be embedded in the application.
    Cobra
    The cobra is an enemy of chap.
    Dashboard
    Creates a dashboard on the GUI which includes: Level number.
    Dialogues
    Create a Dialogue which displays text and then two buttons.
    Direction
    Enum that determines the direction of one of chap's moves
    Exit
    From handout: Once Chap reaches this tile, the game level is finished.
    ExitLock
    From handout: Behaves like a wall time for Chap as long as there are still uncollected treasures.
    FileChooser
    This is a common file chooser for the choosing of JSON files This can be used to choose files for either recording, or to play a saved game
    Free
    From handout: Actors can freely move onto those tiles.
    Gui
    Create a Gui which displays the game on the screen.
    InfoField
    From handout: Like a free tile, but when Chap steps on this field, a help text will be displayed.
    Key
    From Handout: Actors can move onto those tiles.
    Key.Colour  
    Lava
    This tile will kill Chap if he walks on it.
    Level
    Level stores information regarding the details of the level of the game.
    LevelLoader
    LevelLoader contains static methods for loading a level, saving a game, and loading a saved game.
    LockedDoor
    From handout: Chap can only move onto those tiles if they have the key with the matching colour -- this unlocks the door.
    Main
    From Handout: The application window should display the time left to play, the current level, keys collected, and the number of treasures that still need to be collected.
    Maze
    From Handout: The game state is primarily made up of the maze itself, the current location of Chap on the maze, the treasure chest and other items Chap has collected, such as keys.
    Maze.LevelState
    a enum that determines what state the level is in
    MazeTest
    This runs all the tests to ensure the basic logic of the game works
    MenuBar
    Create a MenuBar to be added to the main GUI.
    MonkeyTesting
    class made to test application of game built of intelligent and random testing
    Music
    Objects of this class represent music to play in the game.
    PersistenceTest
    Persistence test contains all the tests for the persistence module.
    Player
    From Handout: The hero of the game.
    RecordAndPlay
    This is a class with static methods for starting a recording, and loading/saving a recording to a file in JSON format It can also start the playback of a recording, assuming there is one saved to play
    RecordedMove
    A representation a move for recording/playback purposes, maps the index of this move with various things.
    ReplayDialogCreator
    Interface for replay dialogs
    ReplayModes
    Enum for the different replay modes
    ReplayOptionDialog
    Create a Dialogue which displays text and then two buttons
    ReplayOptionsCreator
    Button options for replaying a game, ie: auto play, speed options, and step by step
    Sound
    Objects of this class represent a sound to play in the game.
    SoundEffect
    Objects of this class are sound effects to be used in the game.
    StepByStepDialogCreator
    Creates the step by step dialog for step by step playback
    Tile
    Tile class declares all of the required fields and methods for any tile on the maze.
    Tiles
    This class controls the 2D array of tiles for the maze an associated logic
    Treasure
    From handout: If Chap steps onto the tile, the treasure (chip) is picked up and added to the treasure chest.
    Wall
    From handout: Part of a wall, actors cannot move onto those tiles.
